name: orangefeel-back
description: OrangeFeel is a microservices-based application built with Spring Boot, designed for managing digital documents and galleries efficiently.

name: ROBOT-APP-CICD
description: This is a Robot shopping e-commerce application which contains multiple microservices and deployed using Jenkins and ArgoCD tools.

name: Simple-Voting-APP-ArgoCD
description: The repo contains a simple voting application which is developed using microservice and deployed using Jenkins CI/CD pipeline and ArgoCD.

name: GymVietAI-AI
description: This repository contains the code for the AI microservice responsible for predicting personalized workout plans, nutrition recommendation within the GymVietAI application.

name: TaskForge
description: TaskForge - project built on a microservice architecture with Django REST Framework. The platform enables to create groups, assign tasks, track progress. It features JWT authentication, Redis caching, PostgreSQL for data storage, and Cloudinary for image management, showcasing a scalable and modern application design.

name: Carties
description: Carties is a microservices-based web application designed to support car auctions website. Built with a .NET backend and Next.js frontend, the application utilizes Docker, Kubernetes, RabbitMQ, IdentityServer, and Microsoft YARP for service communication, authentication, and real-time updates.

name: grocery-finder
description: A microservices-based application that helps users find the best grocery prices across different stores. The system aggregates pricing data, provides price comparisons, and offers predictive insights using machine learning.

name: template-spring-java-base
description: A robust and customizable template for Java Spring Boot applications, designed to accelerate your development process. This template is pre-configured with essential tools, security configurations, and project structures to help you start building RESTful APIs or microservices applications with Spring Boot.

name: Library
description: This repository contains a collection of common definitions and utilities for all microservices within the Finance Budget Control application. Designed to ensure consistency and code reuse, this library facilitates the integration and maintenance of financial functionalities

license.name: GNU Affero General Public License v3.0

name: SpringBoot2024
description: A Spring Boot application demonstrating RESTful web services, microservices architecture, and database integration. This project showcases essential features like user authentication, CRUD operations, and secure API endpoints. Built with Java, Spring Framework, and JPA for seamless data management.

name: INGSW-Project
description: An Android application developed with Node.js, Express, and Flutter, designed to facilitate real-time online auctions. Users can create listings, place bids, and complete transactions, with a microservices architecture supported by PostgreSQL and Docker containers. Built for the Software Engineering course at the University of Naples "Federico II."

name: city-transit-hub
description: City Transit Hub is a modular microservices-based application designed to explore service discovery and load balancing using Eureka and Spring Boot. This project simulates a dynamic system for locating and managing city transport services, such as buses, taxis, and bike-sharing stations, with a scalable and resilient architecture.

name: react_front_end
description: This project is implemented in React.js and serves as the front-end microservice for the backend repository (https://github.com/mahsahakimi/express_back_end). It is a web application designed for both playing and learning, where teachers can create problems for students, and students can answer them to earn scores.
